summary:
Passionate MSc Marketing Management graduate from Rotterdam School of Management, with comprehensive business background and broad international & project experience, aiming to pursue professional career in marketing-related domains. Creative, open-minded, thinking out-of-the-box, and communicative team player. Self-driven, results-oriented, and always ready to embrace new exciting challenges. 

I fluently speak English, French and Polish. I can smoothly work both individually as well as in a team. I always aim to deliver the highest possible value of tasks.

Throughout my entire higher education studies I was always very active and eager to gain new experiences and expand my horizons. I completed a study exchange at ESSEC Business School in France, co-organized several prestigious events, attended network meetings organized by my students’ associations, fulfilled mentor’s role to international students, as well as pursued internship at Accenture. Participating in all those activities helped me develop a lot of interpersonal and soft skills connected with teamwork, project management, pitching ideas and communication.

I am eager to collaborate in multi-cultural teams & bring innovative and inspiring ideas into effect.
